                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d675">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/689</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-07-27T13:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 27, 1917, 1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received July 27, 12.30 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6826. Your 5173, July 20, 3 p.m. Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HA1">Arthur
                        Henderson</persName> states that the Stockholm conference will be held with
                    the full approval of the Provisional Government in Russia; that the British
                    Labor Party have decided in principle to support this conference; and that a
                    national British Labor conference’ will be held in August to select
                    representatives and to give them their mandate. German intrigue will undoubtedly
                    be attempted, though to what extent it is impossible as yet to foretell.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PWH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
